-- Sheridan Partners Raises $1.8 Billion to Buy Mature U.S. Oil, Gas Fields
-- B y   N o a h   B u h a y a r
-- 2010-11-29T14:58:48Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-29/sheridan-partners-raises-1-8-billion-to-buy-mature-u-s-oil-gas-fields.html
Sheridan Production Partners , the
production company co-founded by private-equity firm Warburg
Pincus LLC, has raised $1.8 billion to invest in onshore oil and
natural-gas properties in the U.S.  The money comes from the sale of limited partner interests
in Sheridan Production Partners II, its second fund aimed at
onshore energy production, according to a statement today.
Sheridan, based in Houston, was formed in 2006 to invest in
mature U.S. oil and gas properties, according to its website.  Sheridan plans to buy properties to add to its holdings in
Oklahoma, Texas and New Mexico, and expand operations to East
Texas, Louisiana and the Rocky Mountain region, Chief Executive
Officer  Lisa Stewart  said in the statement.  The company produced about 19,000 net barrels of oil
equivalent a day and had 127 million barrels in reserve as of
Sept. 30, according to the statement.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
